project.project_abstract: Agronomic evaluation of selected groundnut genotypes under farmers' conditions in the Guinea and Sudan savannah of Ghana using the tricot approach. These genotypes posses various useful traits such as drought tolerance, high oils contents with oleic proportion over 80% and leaf spot tolerance.
project.project_tags: GHANA, CSIR-SARI, TRICOT, ON-FARM, GROUNDNUT, 2021, DROUGHT TOLERANCE, HIGH OLEIC, LEAF SPOTS
